Fast-rising Afrobeat singer Benneth Ajoku Akachukwu, popularly known as Benneto has set high standards for himself as he strives to carve a desired niche for himself on the ever competitive Nigerian music scene. The burgeoning musician who hails from Imo State but was born in Enugu State in Nigeria says music is a tool he uses to express himself and also to tell his many life experiences as a young man.   T-Classic opens up on food poisoning experience     TuneCore announces plans to fuel constant music creation     Dadaboy Ehiz succeeds DJ Cuppy as host of Africa Now Radio   When asked about who inspired him into making music, Benneto who attended Command Day Secondary School, Enugu and is currently an undergraduate said that Wizkid and Iceprince inspired him into becoming a musician. Benneto, who derived his stage name from his first name Benneth also added during an interview that he admires popular Nigerian musician, David Adeleke aka Davido so much because he took the business of music to the next level. The talented Afropop singer who has waxed a handful of singles said that he would in the future like to collaborate with American R&B singer Chris Brown and Nigeriaâ€™s Tekno because of their musical skills and creativity.